{
  "texts": [
    "Yet, a joint consideration of the lower accuracy (∼30%) suggests that FrozenBiLM converges less to the wrong answers.",
    "Together with the observations of (Agrawal et al., 2016) for CNN+RNN and attention models, it seems that models with better accuracy are less likely to predict wrong answers even with incomplete question inputs.",
    "Additionally, Video-LLMs achieve higher MCQA accuracy (e.g., ∼60% of SeViLA) even without the questions.",
    "This result echoes our findings in Sec.",
    "3.6 on video-answer short-cuts for decision making."
  ]
}